    • Method Detail

      • createGameLevel

        public WrappedResponse<GameLevelResponse> createGameLevel(Long accountId,
                                                 String appKey,
                                                 String name,
                                                 String description,
                                                 Enums.GameDifficulty difficulty,
                                                 AppVersion appVersion,
                                                 Long assetImageId,
                                                 Long assetIconId,
                                                 String gameData,
                                                 String gameDataSuffix,
                                                 Enums.Visibility visibility,
                                                 Boolean friendGroup,
                                                 List<Long> connectionIds,
                                                 List<Long> connectionGroupIds,
                                                 Double balance,
                                                 Boolean active,
                                                 Boolean allocateTickets)
                                                   throws SirqulException
        Create a game level. Currently does NOT support game objects.

        Target API Endpoint: /level/create
        Parameters:
        accountId - The logged in user.
        appKey - The game application key to save the level for.
        name - The name of the level.
        description - The description of the level.
        difficulty - The difficulty, possible values are: VERY_EASY, EASY, MEDIUM, HARD, VERY_HARD.
        appVersion - The version number of the application required to correctly load/play the level.
        assetImageId - The asset Id of the level image.
        assetIconId - The asset Id of the level icon.
        gameData - The game level data: xml, json, or other text based format.
        gameDataSuffix - The game level data format type.
        visibility - Is the level visible to others, possible values are: PUBLIC, PRIVATE.
        friendGroup - Make the level be readable by all friends.
        connectionIds - Make the level be readable by connections in this list.
        connectionGroupIds - Make the level be readable by connection groups in this list.
        balance - Set the amount of money available to spend, once 0 deactivate level. Set to a negative value for unlimited.
        active - If true set the game level as active. Default is false.
        allocateTickets - If true then scoring will give tickets. Default is false.
        Returns:
        error SirqulResponse, success a WrappedResponse < GameLevelResponse>
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

        Target API Endpoint: /level/get
        Parameters:

        levelId - The id of the level to return.
        includeGameData - If true include the game level data, otherwise don't. default is false.

        error SirqulResponse, success a WrappedResponse < GameLevelResponse>
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • getGameLevelsByApplication

        public WrappedResponse<GameLevelListResponse> getGameLevelsByApplication(Long accountId,
                                                                String appKey,
                                                                String keyword,
                                                                Integer start,
                                                                Integer limit,
                                                                AppVersion appVersion,
                                                                Boolean includeGameData)
                                                                  throws SirqulException
        Get a list of levels for an application, just those the account has permissions to view.

        Target API Endpoint: /level/search
        Parameters:
        accountId - The logged in user.
        appKey - the app key
        keyword - Match the keyword to the owner name or level name.
        start - Start the result set at some index.
        limit - Limit the result to some number.
        appVersion - The maximum version of the level to return.
        includeGameData - If true include the game level data, otherwise don't. default is false.
        Returns:
        error SirqulResponse, success a WrappedResponse < GameLevelListResponse>
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • getGameLevelsByBillableEntity

        public WrappedResponse<GameLevelListResponse> getGameLevelsByBillableEntity(Long accountId,
                                                                   String appKey,
                                                                   String keyword,
                                                                   Enums.GameLevelApiMap sortField,
                                                                   Boolean descending,
                                                                   Boolean activeOnly,
                                                                   Integer start,
                                                                   Integer limit)
                                                                     throws SirqulException
        Searches on game levels that the logged in user has access to. A user would have access if the creator of the game level is managed under the same BillableEntity.

        Target API Endpoint: /level/searchByBillableEntity
        Parameters:
        accountId - The account id of the user
        appKey - The application key
        keyword - The keyword used to search
        sortField - The column to sort the search on
        descending - The order to return the search results
        activeOnly - Return only active results
        start - The record to begin the return set on
        limit - The number of records to return
        Returns:
        WrappedResponse<GameLevelListResponse> on valid response, SirqulResponse on invalid response.
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

        Update a game level. Currently does NOT support game objects.

        Target API Endpoint: /level/update

        appKey - the application key to save the level for.
        levelId - If update then include the level Id.
        name - The name of the level.
        description - The description of the level.
        difficulty - The difficulty, possible values are: VERY_EASY, EASY, MEDIUM, HARD, VERY_HARD.
        appVersion - the version number of the application required to correctly load/play the level.
        assetImageId - The asset Id of the level image.
        assetIconId - The asset Id of the level icon.
        gameData - The game level data: xml, json, or other texted based format.
        gameDataSuffix - The game level data format type.
        visibility - Is the level visible to others, possible values are: PUBLIC, PRIVATE.
        friendGroup - Make the level be readable by all friends.
        connectionIds - Make the level be readable by connections in this list.
        connectionGroupIds - Make the level be readable by connection groups in this list.
        balance - Set the amount of money available to spend, once 0 deactivate level.
        active - If true set the game level as active. Default is false.
        allocateTickets - If true then scoring will give tickets.

        error SirqulResponse, success a WrappedResponse <GameLevelResponse>

        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.
